From: Brandon High <759848+highb@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon Jun 01 2026
Subject: [PATCH] request_schema: reach steady state on form fields (IGA-743)

Speakeasy generates the request_schema `fields` list with each field's
`name` as a plain Optional+Computed string. The server ignores the
configured name and regenerates it as `<sanitized display_name>_<0-based
occurrence index>` on every write (pkg/models/request_schema/create.go
ValidateForm), so a configured "field1" perpetually diffs against the
stored "Field_One_0" and churns the whole fields list on every plan.

Two further Speakeasy gaps keep the resource from ever reaching "No
changes" even once the name is stable:
  - the field's nested Optional+Computed sub-attributes (bool_field,
    string_field and its children, etc.) replan as unknown whenever any
    sibling changes, so they never settle; and
  - created_at, field_groups, field_relationships and
    justification_visibility lack the SuppressDiff modifier Speakeasy
    only attaches to `id`, so each replans as "known after apply".

Fix:
  - attach requestschemaplanmodifier.NormalizeFields() to `fields`. It
    keeps the server-normalized name from state when display_name still
    normalizes to it (and leaves the configured value otherwise, since
    Terraform forbids planning an Optional+Computed value that matches
    neither config nor prior state), and copies prior-state values into
    planned-unknown computed leaves across the element tree.
  - attach the existing speakeasy SuppressDiff modifier to created_at,
    field_groups, field_relationships and justification_visibility, the
    same treatment `id` already receives.

The NormalizeFields modifier is hand-written in
internal/planmodifiers/requestschemaplanmodifier/ (outside the
Speakeasy-generated planmodifier packages) so regen does not wipe it;
this patch only reapplies the generated-schema wiring.

Refs: IGA-743
